@node Introduction "Workbench Boot Pictures '95 for AmigaOS 2.0 - 3.1 - Introduction"

Introduction
------------

After the great success of the first series Workbench Boot Pictures '95,
I am proud to present Version 2.0!

This volume contains boot pictures with the Workbench '95 theme for 
AmigaOS's 2.0, 2.1, 3.0 and 3.1.  After positive feedback from the
first collection and suggestions to have them converted for all 
AmigaOS Versions, I decided to make a collection of pictures which 
would be applicable all major OS versions!

Workbench Boot Pictures are simply a collection of 16/256 colour IFF pictures 
for use with Joseph Lunks fabulous utility `BootScreen' and program alike 
(PicBoot), to display a nice start-up image while your Hard Disk is booting.  

`BootScreen' is a program which allows you to display an IFF picture while 
the hard drive is booting, much like the Microsoft Windows logo on the
IBM's.

I was influenced to draw these pictures after seeing the "rip-off" Microsoft 
Boot Pictures that were floating around and I thought the Amiga deserved
it's own exclusive Boot Screens.

So, I started work on some Boot Pictures that was exclusively "Amiga", and
related more to the Amiga OS, with this collection including pictures for
the latest Aniga Operating System, AmigaOS 3.1.

These pictures were drawn by hand exclusively with Deluxe Paint V with
colour touch ups and effects done with Art Department Professional 2.1.3.

Hope you enjoy them :-)

@endnode



@node Description "Workbench Boot Pictures '95 for AmigaOS 2.0 - 3.1 - Description"

Description
-----------

Bellow is a brief description of of the images included in this release of
Workbench Boot Pictures '95 (Volume #5):

AmigaOS20.16	16 Colour, HiRes Laced AmigaOS 2.0 Boot Picture
AmigaOS21.16	16 Colour, HiRes Laced AmigaOS 2.1 Boot Picture
AmigaOS30.256	256 Colour, HiRes Laced  AmigaOS 3.0 Boot Picture
AmigaOS31.256	256 Colour, HiRes Laced  AmigaOS 3.1 Boot Picture
AmigaOS31.16	16 Colour, HiRes Laced AmigaOS 3.1 Boot Picture
Template.16	16 Colour, HiRes Laced Template image 
Template.256	256 Colour, HiRes Laced Template image

Total: 7 pictures.

@endnode



@node Requirements "Workbench Boot Pictures '95 for AmigaOS 2.0 - 3.1 - Requirements"

Requirements
------------

To use these pictures you will need:


* Either A1500/A2000/A2500/A3000 (ECS/OCS/Graphics Card)
	 or
	 A1200/A4000 (AGA/Graphics Card)

* OS 2.0 or better 

* A Hard Disk

* `BootScreen' Version 2.2+ by Joseph Luk (or equivilent).


`BootScreen' is available on Aminet in the utils/boot directory.


@endnode



@node Installation "Workbench Boot Pictures '95 for AmigaOS 2.0 - 3.1 - Installation"

Installation
------------

Firstly, if you have not done so already, you will need to install
`BootScreen', follow the instructions accompanied with the program
related the Install procedure.
 
After extracting the WB_BootPics95Any.lha file (well you must of got this far
if you are reading this guide!...), you will see a number of AmigaOS.. files, 
choose the pictures you want and copy them to your SYS:Prefs/Presets 
directory.  You can do this from the CLI by typing;



     copy <path containing WB BootPics directory> SYS:Prefs/Presets


Or alternatively using a Disk Management Program Like Directory Opus.

After copying these files, load the BootScreen Prefs program in the Prefs 
directory of your SYS: partition and choose the desired Boot Screen
Picture.  You can choose the 'Test' Gadget to preview the picture you
want, then press 'Save' for BootScreen to save your options.

And thats all there is to it!

So next time you boot you machine, your desired boot picture will be
displayed.

@endnode



